02/02/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The country's first parliament made up of 120 representatives of NGOs met on Saturday (31 January) in Skopje. Its task is to monitor and correct government policy in regards to the ultimate goals of NATO and EU membership.
In other news, a new poll published Saturday finds Finance Minister Nikola Popovski is the most popular member of the multiethnic coalition cabinet. Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva and Educational Minister Azis Polozani were second and third, according to the Institute for Sociology and Political Legal Studies. (Dnevnik - 02/02/04; MIA, A1 TV - 31/01/04)
